{"info": {"author": "Evan Widloski", "author_email": "evan@evanw.org", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# remarkable_mouse\n\nUse your reMarkable as a graphics tablet.\n\nSpecial thanks to [canselcik](https://github.com/canselcik/libremarkable) and [LinusCDE](https://github.com/LinusCDE/rmWacomToMouse) for inspiration.\n\n<img src=\"photo.jpg\" width=500>\n\n# Quick Start\n\nOn the host machine\n\n``` bash\npip install remarkable-mouse\nremouse\n```\n\nBy default, `10.11.99.1` is used as the address.  Seems to work pretty well wirelessly, too.\n\n# Examples\n\nspecify address, monitor, orientation, password\n\n``` bash\nremouse --address 192.168.1.1 --orientation right --monitor 1 --password foobar\n```\npasswordless login\n\n``` bash\nssh-keygen -m PEM -t rsa -f ~/.ssh/remarkable -N ''\nssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/remarkable.pub root@10.11.99.1\nremouse --key ~/.ssh/remarkable\n```\n\n# Usage\n\n    usage: remouse [-h] [--debug] [--key PATH] [--password PASSWORD]\n               [--address ADDRESS] [--orientation {vertical,left,right}]\n               [--monitor NUM] [--threshold THRESHOLD] [--evdev]\n\n    use reMarkable tablet as a mouse input\n\n    optional arguments:\n      -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n      --debug               enable debug messages\n      --key PATH            ssh private key\n      --password PASSWORD   ssh password\n      --address ADDRESS     device address\n      --orientation {vertical,left,right}\n      --monitor NUM         monitor to use\n      --threshold THRESHOLD\n                            stylus pressure threshold (default 1000)\n      --evdev               use evdev to support pen tilt (requires root, no OSX\n                        support)\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/evidlo/remarkable_mouse", "keywords": "remarkable tablet evdev", "license": "GPLv3", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "remarkable-mouse", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/remarkable-mouse/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/remarkable-mouse/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/evidlo/remarkable_mouse"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/remarkable-mouse/5.1/", "requires_dist": ["paramiko", "libevdev", "pynput", "screeninfo"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "use reMarkable as a graphics tablet", "version": "5.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>remarkable_mouse</h1>\n<p>Use your reMarkable as a graphics tablet.</p>\n<p>Special thanks to <a href=\"https://github.com/canselcik/libremarkable\" rel=\"nofollow\">canselcik</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/LinusCDE/rmWacomToMouse\" rel=\"nofollow\">LinusCDE</a> for inspiration.</p>\n<img src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/6e8740a493492fb05d800be1967e74998075ce4c/70686f746f2e6a7067\" width=\"500\">\n<h1>Quick Start</h1>\n<p>On the host machine</p>\n<pre>pip install remarkable-mouse\nremouse\n</pre>\n<p>By default, <code>10.11.99.1</code> is used as the address.  Seems to work pretty well wirelessly, too.</p>\n<h1>Examples</h1>\n<p>specify address, monitor, orientation, password</p>\n<pre>remouse --address <span class=\"m\">192</span>.168.1.1 --orientation right --monitor <span class=\"m\">1</span> --password foobar\n</pre>\n<p>passwordless login</p>\n<pre>ssh-keygen -m PEM -t rsa -f ~/.ssh/remarkable -N <span class=\"s1\">''</span>\nssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/remarkable.pub root@10.11.99.1\nremouse --key ~/.ssh/remarkable\n</pre>\n<h1>Usage</h1>\n<pre><code>usage: remouse [-h] [--debug] [--key PATH] [--password PASSWORD]\n           [--address ADDRESS] [--orientation {vertical,left,right}]\n           [--monitor NUM] [--threshold THRESHOLD] [--evdev]\n\nuse reMarkable tablet as a mouse input\n\noptional arguments:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  --debug               enable debug messages\n  --key PATH            ssh private key\n  --password PASSWORD   ssh password\n  --address ADDRESS     device address\n  --orientation {vertical,left,right}\n  --monitor NUM         monitor to use\n  --threshold THRESHOLD\n                        stylus pressure threshold (default 1000)\n  --evdev               use evdev to support pen tilt (requires root, no OSX\n                    support)\n</code></pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7064485, "releases": {"1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "7c051aa6844e006398b34179650aa5af", "sha256": "1d9dd0e76caad0a704ef6f9d3793f12ce843a86d05093b3680034285358b5db7"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "remarkable-mouse-1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "7c051aa6844e006398b34179650aa5af", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 3323, "upload_time": "2019-02-24T09:22:16", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-02-24T09:22:16.600177Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/51/7c/17b94edac2503b8d395ba6ecb527850bf3127aaed73c08f710e91a1c0185/remarkable-mouse-1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "e07fd6fb064707bb2dbea6453dd84ed2", "sha256": "5c2b8c6b86765176740f297409a0ba77e4b2f525763ddc5a0a117891ecab2e89"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "remarkable_mouse-2-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "e07fd6fb064707bb2dbea6453dd84ed2", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 4160, "upload_time": "2019-02-24T23:39:48", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-02-24T23:39:48.703510Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/c5/55/4810bd4d583f95775ab7099ecbec8a1f98e574713e32413c1223341cc825/remarkable_mouse-2-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "582043fbc94cd9db0ab2826716c2c5f9", "sha256": "c89fdc796c73ea4c5da52e174c